    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> into quarters</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pepperoni-and-tomato-chicken-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>tomato paste</strong>,<strong> dried basil</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic </strong>in 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your<strong> tomato stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pepperoni-and-tomato-chicken-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong> to an<strong> oven-proof dish</strong> with the <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Season with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and<strong> sugar </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pepperoni-and-tomato-chicken-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Top the tomato<strong> </strong>sauce<strong> </strong>with your <strong>chicken breast portion[s] </strong>and drizzle the chicken with <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper </strong>and put the dish in the oven for an initial 12 min</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pepperoni-and-tomato-chicken-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>potato[es]</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces and add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pepperoni-and-tomato-chicken-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the potatoes are cooking, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> pepperoni </strong>finely</p><p>Cut your <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways, then slice finely</p><p>Wash your <strong>salad</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pepperoni-and-tomato-chicken-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has had 12 min, remove the dish from the oven and top with your <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped pepperoni</strong></p><p>Return the dish to the oven and cook for a further 12-15 min or until the cheese has melted, the pepperoni has crisped and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy pepperoni chicken</strong></p><p>Combine the <strong>salad</strong>, <strong>sliced cucumber</strong> and your <strong>balsamic vinegar </strong>in a bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>\u2013 this is your <strong>dressed salad</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/cheesy-pepperoni-and-tomato-chicken-with-crispy-sweet-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>cheesy pepperoni chicken</strong> from the dish and give the <strong>tomato sauce</strong> a good mix up</p><p>Serve the <strong>cheesy pepperoni chicken</strong> over the<strong> tomato sauce</strong> with the <strong>crispy potatoes</strong> and <strong>dressed salad</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
